2.00	Buddy_Werner	Buddy Werner	Wallace "Buddy" Werner (February 26, 1936 - April 12, 1964) was an American ski racer in the 1950s and early 1960s. Born and raised in Steamboat Springs, Colorado, Werner and his siblings were accomplished skiers, and competed in both alpine and Nordic events on Howelsen Hill. Werner raced for the University of Colorado in the mid 1950s, making the 1956 Olympic team in his sophomore year, joining his elder sister, Skeeter Werner.	
